Problem Statement¶

Context¶

AllLife Bank wants to focus on its credit card customer base in the next financial year. They have been advised by their marketing research team, that the penetration in the market can be improved. Based on this input, the Marketing team proposes to run personalized campaigns to target new customers as well as upsell to existing customers. Another insight from the market research was that the customers perceive the support services of the back poorly. Based on this, the Operations team wants to upgrade the service delivery model, to ensure that customer queries are resolved faster. Head of Marketing and Head of Delivery both decide to reach out to the Data Science team for help

Objective¶

To identify different segments in the existing customer, based on their spending patterns as well as past interaction with the bank, using clustering algorithms, and provide recommendations to the bank on how to better market to and service these customers.

Data Description¶

The data provided is of various customers of a bank and their financial attributes like credit limit, the total number of credit cards the customer has, and different channels through which customers have contacted the bank for any queries (including visiting the bank, online and through a call center).

Data Dictionary

  • Sl_No: Primary key of the records
  • Customer Key: Customer identification number
  • Average Credit Limit: Average credit limit of each customer for all credit cards
  • Total credit cards: Total number of credit cards possessed by the customer
  • Total visits bank: Total number of Visits that customer made (yearly) personally to the bank
  • Total visits online: Total number of visits or online logins made by the customer (yearly)
  • Total calls made: Total number of calls made by the customer to the bank or its customer service department (yearly)

Questions / Answers¶

  1. How is the distrubution of average credit limit of customer?
  • Very left-skewed with the vast majority having less than $2500 in credit limit.
  1. What percenatage of the customers have never made a service-related call to the bank?
  • Roughly 25% of customers.
  1. What percentage of customers have never logged in to the online portal?
  • Roughly 25% of customers.
  1. How many customers have never visited bank?
  • 100 customers.
  1. How are the different variables correlated with each other?
  • Total amount of credit cards and average amount of credit limit are correlated.
  • Average amount of credit limit and total visits online are somewhat correlated.
  • There is somewhat of a negative correlation between average credit limit, total credit cards, and total visits bank in regards to total calls made.
  • There is also somewhat of a negative correlation between total bank visits to total online visits.

K-means Clustering¶

In [126]:
# find optimal k with elbow method

sum_of_squared = []
k_range = range(1, 11)

for k in k_range:
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=k, n_init=10, random_state=42)
    kmeans.fit(df_pca2)
    sum_of_squared.append(kmeans.inertia_)

plt.plot(k_range, sum_of_squared, marker='o')
plt.xlabel('Number of Clusters (k)')
plt.ylabel('Sum of Squared Distances')
plt.title('Elbow Method for Optimal k')
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

The optimal k is 3.

In [127]:

num_clusters = 3

Actionable Insights and Recommendations¶

We have segmented our customers into three distinct categories based on their credit limits: approximately \$12k, \$33k, and \$140k. Our strategic approach to engaging with each group is as follows:

Customers with approximately $12k credit limit:

We will proactively encourage this segment to embrace online checking to enhance their user experience and convenience. Regular follow-up calls will be made to understand their specific needs better and offer them tailored products and services. Customers with approximately $33k credit limit:

We aim to encourage this group to utilize online checking more frequently, ensuring seamless interactions with our platform. While promoting online usage, we will also prioritize in-person engagements to build strong, personalized relationships and offer our products. Customers with approximately $140k credit limit:

A key focus for this high-value segment will be online advertisements, strategically placed to capture their attention whenever they access our platform. Through targeted marketing campaigns, we will highlight our premium offerings to cater to their distinct requirements. By adopting these specialized approaches, we seek to optimize customer engagement, satisfaction, and ultimately drive growth in our product and service utilization across all credit limit tiers.
